  "texts": [
    "It can be seen that the first two schemes adopt similar design principles that integrate the sensing (communication) capabilities into the communication (radar) systems without significantly degrading the primary functionality.",
    "Although the radar-centric scheme can satisfy the sensing requirement, its achievable communication rate is usually limited by the low radar pulse repetition frequency (PRF).",
    "On the contrary, the communication-centric scheme can guarantee fast and reliable information transmission at the cost of poor sensing capabilities due to the natural randomness of communication signals.",
    "Fortunately, the joint design scheme can maintain a better balance between the two functionalities.",
    "However, it lacks a unified framework and requires more effort to design the hardware architecture and software protocol."
  ],
